content:
I'm trying to access the calendar via the link in the GitHub readme:
https://github.com/rust-lang/wg-traits
https://calendar.google.com/event?action=TEMPLATE&tmeid=MnFmbmdkaGV0aXE3Zjc4cjlpNWVjNDRoZXMgNnU1cnJ0Y2U2bHJ0djA3cGZpM2RhbWdqdXNAZw&tmsrc=6u5rrtce6lrtv07pfi3damgjus%40group.calendar.google.com

On both Firefox and Chrome this leads to a blank Google Calendar page with nothing too interesting in the console log. Is there a better link?

I figured it out, the main compiler team calendar has the wg-traits events:
https://calendar.google.com/calendar/u/0/embed?src=6u5rrtce6lrtv07pfi3damgjus@group.calendar.google.com
The wg-traits link is still broken though, not sure if that should go to the main compiler team one or not.
